    <body>
        <ol>
            <li>After your target has been published, go to Windows Explorer and navigate to the folder where your Zendesk output resides.</li>
            <li>In your Zendesk Help Center dashboard, click the icon to customize the design. The Themes page is displayed.</li>
            <li>Hover over the customized theme, and click <span class="Emphasis">View Theme</span>.</li>
            <li>
                <p>Click <span class="Emphasis">Edit Code</span>.</p>
                <p>
                    <img src="../../../../Images/Flare/Output/Zendesk-Custom-Theme-Edit-Code.png" class="MaxWidth100Percent" />
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>From your Flare project's output folder, add all files  from the assets folder  to Zendesk. </li>
            <li>In the templates subfolder of your theme, open the <b>document_head.hbs</b> file in a text editor.</li>
            <MadCap:pageBreak MadCap:conditions="Flare-Guides.Flare-Whats-New-Guide" />
            <li>
                <p>If you added, deleted, or renamed any of the links listed in this file, update the respective links</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>If you added any new CSS files, add a new &lt;link&gt; tag for each new file.</li>
                    <li>If you added any new JavaScript files, add a new &lt;script&gt; tag for each new file.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>Save the changes in the document_head.hbs file.</li>
            <li>In the top-right corner in the Zendesk Themes page, click <span class="Emphasis">Publish</span>.</li>
        </ol>
        <div class="note">
            <p class="Note-Text">For more information on working with themes in Zendesk, please refer to the Zendesk documentation.</p>
        </div>
    </body>
</html>